# @REPO@ field deploy bundle (@STAGE@)

A self-contained deploy of the image `@IMAGE@`. Everything needed to run it
in the field travels in this folder; the target host does NOT need base's
toolchain, source tree, or `setup.conf`.

## Run it

    ./deploy.sh up      load the image, then `docker compose up -d`
    ./deploy.sh down    `docker compose down`
    ./deploy.sh logs    `docker compose logs` (add `-f` to follow)

`up` docker-loads `image.tar.xz` then starts the resolved `compose.yaml`.
The service uses `restart: unless-stopped`, so it auto-starts on host
reboot; stop it with `./deploy.sh down`.

## Contents

    image.tar.xz   the container image (deploy.sh docker-loads it)
    compose.yaml   fully-resolved, self-contained compose (do NOT edit)
    config/        operator-tunable config copies (see below)
    deploy.sh      this launcher
    README         this file

## Adjusting config in the field (no rebuild)

`config/` holds an editable copy of each file the component declared as
operator-tunable (`config/<component>/deploy.manifest`). Edit a file under
`config/`, then re-run `./deploy.sh up`: the mounted copy wins over the
image's baked default. Files NOT under `config/` are baked-only and require
a rebuild to change.

Do not edit `compose.yaml` -- it is machine-generated and fully resolved.
Adjust behavior through `config/` instead.

## Image identity

The image is tagged `@IMAGE@` (`<repo>:<stage>-<version>`, version from
`git describe`), so loading multiple versions on one host never collides.
